ts%20the%20system%20is%20driving%20workers%20to%20the%20'brink%20of%20frustration.'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222500%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20visitor%20walks%20past%20US%20multinational%20telecommunications%20AT%26amp%3BT%20logo%20during%20the%202024%20Mobile%20World%20Congress%20(MWC)%2C%20the%20telecom%20industry's%20biggest%20annual%20gathering%2C%20in%20Barcelona.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c2e52b57d362d375e7f81e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221666%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAT%26amp%3BT%20uses%20an%20automated%20system%20that%20tracks%20employee%20compliance%20with%20the%20company's%20return-to-office%20policy.%3Cp%3EPau%20Barrena%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAT%26amp%3BT%20is%20dialing%20down%20its%20use%20of%20a%20controversial%20attendance%20tracking%20system%20for%20enforcing%20its%20RTO%20policy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20so-called%20presence%20report%20uses%20a%20combination%20of%20inputs%20to%20log%20employees'%20time%20in%20the%20office.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20company's%20CMO%20says%20its%20goal%20of%20finding%20%26quot%3Bfreeloaders%26quot%3B%20has%20been%20met%2C%20though%20trust%20issues%20remain.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fatt-help-desk-manager-relocation-stankey-memo-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAT%26amp%3BT%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20reducing%20its%20reliance%20on%20an%20employee-attendance%20tracking%20system%2C%20admitting%20to%20workers%20that%20it%20hasn't%20been%20fully%20accurate%20and%20is%20%26quot%3Bdriving%20people%20to%20the%20brink%20of%20frustration.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20system%2C%20known%20internally%20as%20presence%20reporting%2C%20automatically%20tracks%20the%20hours%20workers%20spend%20at%20their%20assigned%20office.%20Most%20are%20required%20to%20log%20at%20least%20eight%20hours%20a%20day%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%2