B%20moment%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20segment%20produces%20some%20funny%20moments%2C%20as%20the%20players%20often%20recall%20big%20hits%20they%20suffered.%20Former%20New%20England%20Patriot%20Rob%20Gronkowski%2C%20for%20example%2C%20got%20put%20on%20the%20ground%20as%20a%20rookie%20by%20teammate%20Vince%20Wilfork%20during%20a%20practice.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20there's%20a%20lower%20likelihood%20of%20being%20brutally%20tackled%20on%20the%20job%20at%20a%20bank%20or%20a%20hedge%20fund%2C%20we%20thought%20it'd%20be%20fun%20to%20pose%20the%20question%20to%20financial%20pros%3A%20What%20was%20their%20%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20Wall%20Street%26quot%3B%20moment%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20all%2C%20a%20career%20on%20Wall%20Street%20is%20full%20of%20colorful%20moments.%20Unseen%20threats%20can%20suddenly%20throw%20financial%20markets%20into%20chaos%2C%20and%20strong%20personalities%20can%20make%20for%20memorable%20office%20dynamics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBelow%2C%20we've%20compiled%20stories%20from%20five%20Wall%20Street%20vets%20who%20regaled%20us%20with%20some%20of%20their%20most%20lasting%20early-career%20memories%2C%20which%20came%20during%20some%20of%20the%20market's%20most%20famous%20%E2%80%94%20and%20infamous%20%E2%80%94%20episodes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3ELehman%20Brothers%20failure%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22People%20stand%20next%20to%20windows%20above%20an%20exterior%20sign%20at%20the%20Lehman%20Brothers%20headquarters%20in%20New%20York%20in%20this%20September%2016%2C%202008%20file%20photo.%20September%2014%2C%202009%20marks%20the%20one%20year%20anniversary%20of%20the%20bankruptcy%20filing%20of%20Lehman%20Brothers.%20Picture%20taken%20September%2016%2C%202008.%20%20REUTERS%2FChip%20East%2FFiles%20%20(UNITED%20STATES%20BUSINESS%20EMPLOYMENT%20ANNIVERSARY)%20-%20RTR27S6Z%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5745ef485124c9fd0a96a0cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22581%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFile%20photo%20of%20people%20at%20Lehman%20Brothers%20headquarters%20in%20New%20York%3Cp%3EThomson%20Reuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EMo%20Haghbin%2C%20the%20head%20of%20strategic%20ETFs%20at%20ProShares%2C%20said%20he%20was%20managing%20the%20trading%20operations%20desk%20for%20the%20fixed-income%20hedge%20fund%20at%20Barclays%20Global%20Investors%20in%202008.%20He%20oversaw%20margin%20movement%2C%20and%20Lehman%20Brothers%20was%20one%20of%20his%20counterparties.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20day%2C%20payments%20from%20Lehman%20stopped%20coming%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLeading%20up%20to%20the%20weekend%20when%20Lehman%20collapsed%2C%20margin%20calls%20from%20our%20side%20weren't%20being%20answered.%20We%20would%20send%20money%20out.%20We%20would%20ask%20for%20money%20in%2C%20and%20we%20wouldn't%20get%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20thought%20it%20must%20be%20an%20administrative%20error.%20But%20as%20we%20all%20know%2C%20it's%20because%20there%20was%20a%20liquidity%20issue%20and%20they%20didn't%20have%20the%20cash%20to%20deliver.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWithin%20a%20week%2C%20chaos%20broke%20out%20at%20Barclays%20and%20across%20the%20rest%20of%20Wall%20Street%20as%20Lehman%20Brothers%20went%20under.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20weekend%20when%20everything%20happened%2C%20we%20were%20in%20the%20office%20at%204%20am%2C%26quot%3B%20Haghbin%20said.%20%26quot%3BThey%20had%20these%20'war%20rooms'%20%E2%80%94%20really%20crisis%20rooms.%20We%20spent%20days%20in%20that%20room.%20People%20were%20buying%20extra%20shirts%20and%20clothes%20rather%20than%20going%20home.%20Everyone%20was%20working%2024%20hours%20a%20day.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20in%20particular%20that%20Haghbin%20remembers%20about%20that%20time%20is%20how%20the%20corporate%20hierarchy%20broke%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20amazing%20how%20things%20change%20in%20terms%20of%20visibility%20and%20seniority.%20There%20was%20no%20junior%20person%2C%20senior%20person%20%E2%80%94%20everybody%20was%20working%20on%20things.%20Managing%20directors%20working%20with%20analysts%20to%20solve%20problems.%20Titles%20were%20out%20the%20door%2C%20hierarchy%20out%20the%20door%2C%20everyone%20just%20trying%20to%20solve%20a%20problem.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20Bernie%20Madoff%20scandal%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Bernie%20Madoff%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5e3c8747d9db1d4cb06d3597%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222562%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EFinancier%20Bernard%20Madoff%20arrives%20at%20Manhattan%20Federal%20court%20on%20March%2012%2C%202009%20in%20New%20York%20City.%20Madoff%20is%20scheduled%20to%20enter%20a%20guilty%20plea%20on%2011%20felony%20counts%20which%20under%20federal%20law%20can%20result%20in%20a%20sentence%20of%20about%20150%20years.%3Cp%3EStephen%20Chernin%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EBen%20McMillan%2C%20CIO%20at%20IDX%20Advisors%2C%20started%20his%20career%20as%20a%20quant%20at%20American%20Express%2C%20but%20moved%20to%20an%20analyst%20role%20at%20Lyster%20Watson%20in%20early%202008.%20While%20it%20was%20obviously%20a%20volatile%20year%20in%20markets%2C%20he%20said%20the%20memory%20that%20sticks%20out%20the%20most%20is%20when%20he%20heard%20Bernie%20Madoff%20was%20charged%20with%20defrauding%20investors%20in%20December%202008.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20guy%20that%20hired%20me%2C%20Mark%20Fried%2C%20was%20actually%20one%20of%20the%20guys%20from%20%3Cem%3ELiar's%20Poker%3C%2Fem%3E%2C'%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20referencing%20Michael%20Lewis'%20book.%20%26quot%3BI'll%20never%20forget%2C%20I%20was%20a%20twenty-something%20analyst%2C%20and%20he%20was%20sitting%20at%20the%20Bloomberg%20terminal.%20He%20goes%2C%20'Charlie%2C%20they%20finally%20got%20Bernie%2C'%26quot%3B%20talking%20to%20another%20portfolio%20manager.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMcMillan%20said%20that%20the%20consensus%20on%20Wall%20Street%20at%20the%20time%20was%20that%20Madoff%20was%20%26quot%3Bfront%20running%26quot%3B%20clients%2C%20or%20illegally%20buying%20shares%20of%20a%20company%20that%20its%20client%20was%20about%20to%20purchase%2C%20benefitting%20from%20the%20subsequent%20upward%20move%20in%20the%20stock%20price.%20So%20when%20it%20was%20revealed%20that%20it%20was%20actually%20a%20Ponzi%20scheme%2C%20his%20colleagues%20didn't%20initially%20believe%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20it%20was%20a%20Ponzi's%20team%20is%20just%20so%20outlandish%20that%20everybody%20assumed%20that%20the%20article%20had%20got%20it%20wrong%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EBlack%20Monday%2C%201987%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222953%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Trader%20looks%20at%20computer%20at%20the%20Pacific%20Stock%20Exchange%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20on%20Black%20Monday%201987%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F680947593fe8d3928363e245%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222014%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20trader%20looks%20at%20a%20computer%20at%20the%20Pacific%20Stock%20Exchange%20in%20Los%20Angeles%20on%20Black%20Monday%2C%201987.%3Cp%3ELennox%20McLendon%2FAP%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Rosenberg's%20%26quot%3BWelcome%20to%20Wall%20Street%26quot%3B%20moment%20came%20quick%20%E2%80%94%20like%20first%20day%20on%20the%20job%20quick.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20October%2019%2C%201987%2C%20otherwise%20known%20as%20%26quot%3BBlack%20Monday%2C%26quot%3B%20when%20the%20S%26amp%3BP%20500%20fell%2020%25%20in%20a%20day.%20Rosenberg%20had%20just%20started%20his%20job%20as%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Bank%20of%20Nova%20Scotia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20career%20was%20born%20into%20a%20complete%20state%20of%20mayhem%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20day%20of%20anxiety%20taken%20to%20an%20extreme%20%E2%80%94%20nothing%20I%20saw%20again%20until%20the%20Great%20Financial%20Crisis.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERosenberg%20said%20the%20experience%20taught%20him%20the%20value%20that%20economists%20can%20provide%20to%20traders%20and%20investors%2C%20especially%20during%20volatile%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20followed%20the%20chief%20economist%20and%20assistant%20chief%20economist%20around%20all%20day%2C%20through%20the%20trading%20room%20and%20up%20to%20the%20executive%20offices%2C%20armed%20with%20charts%20and%20talking%20about%20liquidity%2C%20the%20economy%2C%20and%20how%20it%20all%20related%20to%20markets.%20They%20were%20trying%20to%20convince%20everyone%20the%20sky%20wasn't%20falling%20and%20there%20wouldn't%20be%20a%20destabilizing%20depression%20%E2%80%94%20and%20let%20me%20tell%20you%2C%20that%20day%20was%20frightening%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20term%20'cool%20economist'%20wasn't%20an%20oxymoron%20%E2%80%94%20my%20two%20superiors%20were%20cool%20as%20cucumbers%20while%20everyone%20else%20ran%20around%20like%20a%20chicken%20with%20its%20head%20cut%20off%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20continued.%20%26quot%3BI%20learned%20early%20that%20the%20role%20of%20the%20economist%20is%20to%20provide%20stability%20to%20traders%2C%20salespeople%2C%20and%20management%20when%20things%20are%20incredibly%20unstable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3E1998%20Russian%20credit%20default%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22This%20photograph%20taken%20on%20April%2012%2C%202023%2C%20shows%20Russian%20national%20flag%20is%20pictured%20atop%20the%20Russian%20Central%20Bank%20headquarters%20in%20downtown%20Moscow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67c474a769253ccddf9804dc%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22667%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThis%20photograph%20taken%20on%20April%2012%2C%202023%2C%20shows%20Russian%20national%20flag%20is%20pictured%20atop%20the%20Russian%20Central%20Bank%20headquarters%20in%20downtown%20Moscow.%3Cp%3EKirill%20KUDRYAVTSEV%20%2F%20AFP%3C%2F