0that%20could%20turn%20him%20into%20a%20trillionaire.%20Perhaps%20by%20accident%2C%20it%20may%20have%20also%20invented%20an%20alter%20ego%20for%20one%20of%20Musk's%20other%20major%20holdings%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fxai-management-shakeup-data-annotation-team-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3ExAI%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAcross%2016%20pages%20of%20its%20September%205%20proxy%20statement%2C%20the%20automaker%20detailed%20a%20plan%20centered%20on%20targets%20for%20earnings%20and%20growth%20in%20key%20product%20lines%20that%20could%20result%20in%20Musk%20owning%20more%20than%20a%20quarter%20of%20what%20would%20be%20an%20%248.5%20trillion%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20explaining%20its%20position%2C%20Tesla%20noted%20that%20Musk%20has%20built%20several%20very%20valuable%20companies%3A%20%26quot%3BSpace%20Exploration%20Technologies%20Corp.%2C%20Neuralink%20Corp.%20and%20eXploratory%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20or%20'xAI.'%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221766%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20screenshot%20of%20Tesla's%20Septmber%205%2C%202025%20proxy%20statement%2C%20with%20the%20phrase%20%26quot%3BeXploratory%20Artificial%20Intelligence%20or%20'xAI'%26quot%3B%20underlined%20and%20indicated%20with%20an%20arrow.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c32db057d362d375e801c7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22766%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAn%20excerpt%20from%20Tesla's%20September%205%2C%202025%20proxy%20statement.%3Cp%3ETesla%3B%20Sophie%20Kleeman%2FBI%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20referred%20to%20the%20company%20simply%20as%20xAI%2C%20or%20by%20its%20legal%20name%2C%20X.AI%20Corp.%2C%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20document.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20wrinkle%3F%20Neither%20Musk%20nor%20xAI%20appears%20to%20have%20publicly%20claimed%20that%20the%20company's%20name%20stands%20for%20%26quot%3BeXploratory%20artificial%20intelligence.%26quot%3B%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20name%20doesn't%20appear%20to%20stand%20for%20anything%20at%20all.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phrase%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20artificial%20intelligence%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20AI%26quot%3B%20doesn't%20appear%20on%20xAI's%20website%2C%20any%20of%20its%20public%20securities%20filings%2C%20the%20Nevada%20articles%20of%20incorporation%20of%20X.AI%20Corp.%2C%20filings%20in%20any%20federal%20lawsuit%20to%20which%20xAI%20is%20a%20party%2C%20or%20any%20other%20xAI-related%20news%20articles%2C%20press%20releases%2C%20or%20public%20filings%20reviewed%20by%20Business%20Insider.%20These%20sources%20instead%20refer%20to%20the%20company%20as%20xAI%20or%20its%20legal%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20phrases%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20artificial%20intelligence%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20AI%26quot%3B%20don't%20appear%20to%20be%20used%20frequently%20online.%20A%20few%20companies%20have%20referred%20to%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20AI%20initiatives%26quot%3B%20in%20press%20releases%20or%20public%20filings%2C%20and%20a%20few%20academics%20have%20used%20the%20initials%20%26quot%3BXAI%26quot%3B%20to%20refer%20to%20%26quot%3Bexplainable%26quot%3B%20or%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%26quot%3B%20AI%20in%20papers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20posts%20on%20niche%20blogs%20claim%20that%20the%20name%20of%20Musk's%20AI%20company%20is%20shorthand%20for%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20they%20don't%20cite%20sources.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20words%20have%20occasionally%20been%20strung%20together%20on%20social%20media.%20Musk's%20chatbot%20Grok%20used%20the%20term%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20AI%26quot%3B%20in%20nine%20separate%20X%20posts%20in%20July%20and%20August%202025%2C%20accounting%20for%20nearly%20all%20uses%20of%20the%20term%20on%20X%20during%20that%20time%2C%20though%20never%20as%20another%20name%20for%20xAI%2C%20a%20search%20shows.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplatform.twitter.com%2Fwidgets.js%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%3EThe%20fourth%20xAI%20companion%20is%20Isaac%2C%20inspired%20by%20sci-fi%20author%20Isaac%20Asimov.%20He's%20featured%20in%20the%20Tesla%20Diner%20video%20with%20Ani%2C%20Rudi%2C%20and%20Valentine%2C%20emphasizing%20exploratory%20AI%20interactions.%3C%2Fp%3E%E2%80%94%20Grok%20(%40grok)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fgrok%2Fstatus%2F1948474560862367811%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJuly%2024%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ETesla%20and%20xAI%20didn't%20respond%20to%20emailed%20questions%20about%20whether%20xAI%20stands%20for%20%26quot%3Bexploratory%20artificial%20intelligence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX.AI%20Corp.%20was%20formed%20in%20Nevada%20in%20March%202023.%20Musk%20announced%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20company%20in%20an%20audio%20livestream%20in%20July.%20The%20AI%20company%20merged%20with%20Musk's%20social-media%20company%20X.%20Corp.%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20overarching%20goal%20of%20xAI%20is%20to%20build%20a%20good%20AGI%20with%20the%20overarching%20purpose%20of%20just%20trying%20to%20understand%20the%20universe%2C%26quot%3B%20Musk%20said%20on%20the%20livestream%2C%20using%20an%20acronym%20for%20artificial%20general%20intelligence.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20thing%20is%20clear%3A%20Musk%20really%20likes%20the%20letter%20%26quot%3BX.%26quot%3B%20Space%20Exploration%20Technologies%20Corp.%2C%20his%20second-most%20valuable%20company%2C%20is%20known%20as%20SpaceX.%20One%20of%20Tesla's%20top-selling%20cars%20is%20the%20Model%20X%2C%20and%20one%20of%20his%20children%20was%20named%20X%20%C3%86%20A-12%20(now%20known%20by%20the%20nickname%20%26quot%3BX.%26quot%3B).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EX.com%20was%20also%20the%20name%20of%20a%20financial%20technology%20company%20Musk%20co-founded%20in%201999.%20It%20eventually%20became%20PayPal%3B%20Musk%20bought%20the%20domain%20name%20X.com%20back%20in%202017%20and%2C%20after%20buying%20Twitter%20in%202022%2C%20he%20moved%20it%20to%20X.com.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EHave%20a%20tip%3F%20Know%20more%3F%20Reach%20Jack%20Newsham%20via%20email%20(%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22mailto%3Ajnewsham%40businessinsider.com%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ejnewsham%40businessinsider.com%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E)%20or%20via%20Signal%20(%2B1-314-971-1627).%20Do%20not%20use%20a%20work%20device%20or%20work%20WiFi.%20Use%20a%20personal%20email%20address%2C%20a%20nonwork%20device%2C%20and%20nonwork%20WiFi%3B%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Finsider-guide-to-securely-sharing-whistleblower-information-about-powerful-institutions-2021-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3Ehere's%20our%20guide%20to%20sharing%20information%20securely%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-xai-exploratory-ai-grok-2025-9%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1757668201000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c32f70f9db348adc0b514b%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-xai-exploratory-ai-grok-2025-9%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22In%20a%20recent%20proxy%20statement%20about%20Elon%20Musk's%20compensation%20package%2C%20Tesla%20said%20xAI's%20name%20stood%20for%20%26quot%3BeXploratory%20Artificial%20Intelligence.%26quot%3B%20Huh%3F%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22jnewsham%40insider.com%20(Jack%20Newsham)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A29%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftesla-xai-exploratory-ai-grok-2025-9%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22I%20was%20called%20back%20into%20the%20JPMorgan%20office.%20My%20family%20has%20had%20to%20adjust%2C%20but%20I%20trust%20the%20company.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22851%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22a%20man%20posing%20near%20the%20ocean%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68c307d5f9db348adc0b4bde%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22638%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJitender%20Jain.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Jitender%20Jain%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EJitender%20Jain%20transitioned%20to%20a%20hybrid%20role%20at%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20after%20Walmart's%20office%20closure.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EHe%20goes%20to%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%2C%20and%20he%20and%20his%20wife%20navigate%20parenting%20and%20cleaning%20accordingly.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EJain%20values%20in-person%20work%20for%20stronger%20connections%20and%20broader%20economic%20contributions.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20as-told-to%20essay%20is%20based%20on%20a%20conversation%20with%20Jitender%20Jain%2C%20a%2040-year-old%20principal%20software%20engineer%20at%20JPMorgan%20Chase%20and%20a%20father%20of%20two%20daughters%20in%20Dallas.%20The%20following%20has%20been%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20when%20I%20worked%20at%20Walmart%20Global%20Tech%2C%20the%20company%20suddenly%20announced%20it%20was%20closing%20its%20Dallas%20office.%20I%20was%20told%20I'd%20have%20to%20relocate%20to%20another%20state%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frto-mandates-driving-workers-quit-helping-employers-avoid-layoffs-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereturn%20to%20the%20office%20full%20time%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wasn't%20ready%20to%20transition%20from%20working%20from%20home%20to%20moving%20to%20a%20new%20state%20and%20going%20to%20the%20office%20daily%2C%20so%20I%20took%20severance%20from%20Walmart%20and%20transitioned%20to%20a%20hybrid%20role%20as%20a%20principal%20software%20engineer%20at%20JPMorgan%20Chase.%20A%20colleague%20referred%20me%20for%20the%20position%2C%20and%20after%20multiple%20rounds%20of%20interviews%2C%20I%20accepted%20the%20offer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAround%20the%20same%20time%2C%20my%20wife's%20team%20was%20called%20back%20to%20the%20office%20three%20days%20a%20week%20and%20was%20reduced%20from%20nine%20to%20just%20three%20engineers%2C%20tripling%20her%20workload.%20Life%20throws%20curveballs%2C%20but%20after%20navigating%20COVID-19%2C%20we%20felt%20equipped%20to%20handle%20the%20transition%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20some%20thoughtful%20planning%20around%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fworking-remotely-childcare-costs-career-growth-return-to-office-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Echildcare%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20we%20were%20able%20to%20manage%2C%20though%20there%20were%20challenges%2C%20and%20we're%20still%20getting%20used%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22f7cbab3f-357c-48c8-9324-a4ad92ca9ad8%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20work%20three%20days%20in%20the%20office%20and%20two%20from%20home%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20days%20are%20fixed%20team%20days%20we%20agreed%20on%20together%2C%20and%20the%20third%20is%20flexible.%20I%20go%20to%20the%20office%20on%20Monday%2C%20Tuesday%2C%20and%20Thursday.%20Many%20JPMorgan%20employees%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjp-morgan-rto-mandate-worried-damage-relationship-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecalled%20back%20to%20the%20office%20five%20days%20a%20week%3C%2Fa%3E.%20My%20commute%20is%20only%20about%2015-20%20minutes%20each%20way%2C%20which%20is%20manageable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20know%20others%20have%20it%20harder.%20There%20are%20people%20who%20bought%20homes%20farther%20away%20during%20the%20pandemic%20because%20of%20cost%20or%20space.%20I%20remember%20leadership%20saying%20early%20on%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20won't%20be%20remote%20forever%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20I%20took%20that%20seriously.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2299605a04-ab5a-4811-b77b-56821cfe592d%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ETruth%20be%20told%2C%20working%20from%20home%20during%20COVID-19%20and%20even%20after%20wasn't%20exactly%20enjoyable%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20all%20remote%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20would%20sometimes%20both%20have%20meetings%20at%20the%20same%20time%2C%20so%20we'd%20each%20have%20to%20close%20our%20doors%20and%20hope%20for%20the%20best.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20our%20daughters%2C%208%20and%2013%2C%20would%20be%20playing%20outside%20the%20rooms%2C%20and%20that%20play%20would%20eventually%20turn%20into%20a%20quarrel%20over%20the%20same%20toy%20or%20game.%20That's%20when%20I'd%20have%20to%20jump%20in%20and%20help.%20I%20would%20rather%20be%20at%20the%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20send%20the%20kids%20to%20school%20and%20then%20to%20aftercare.%20In%20the%20summer%2C%20they%20attended%20day%20camps.%20My%20wife%20and%20I%20coordinate%20pickup%20and%20drop-off.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d3a8c19e-649c-4100-8abd-b5e67478fd82%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20learned%20to%20share%20household%20responsibilities%20during%20the%20pandemic%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20doing%20things%20like%20cooking%20and%20doing%20the%20dishes.%20To%20be%20honest%2C%20I%20was%20forced%20into%20it%20at%20first%2C%20but%20over%20time%2C%20I've%20gotten%20used%20to%20it%20so%20that%20now%2C%20when%20a%20child%20is%20sick%20or%20has%20an%20appointment%2C%20my%20wife%20and%20I%20trade%20off%20based%20on%20our%20schedules.%20It's%20helping%20everyone%20%E2%80%94%20not%20just%20my%20wife%20but%20the%20whole%20family%20%E2%80%94%20because%20we're%20all%20happier%20when%20she%20gets%20more%20time%20to%20follow%20her%20passions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20we%20were%20all%20at%20home%2C%20most%20of%20the%20work%20and%20meals%20happened%20in%20the%20house%2C%20so%20there%20were%20a%20lot%20more%20chores.%20Now%20that%20we're%20out%20during%20the%20day%2